            "answer_text": "Yes Although the Avestan script has many letters that would be left without use, the Avestan script works perfectly for modern Persian with modifications. As pointed out by Lara Novakov (\u10da\u10d0\u10e0\u10d0 \u10dc\u10dd\u10d5\u10d0\u10d9\u10dd\u10d5) there is a Avestan based script made specifically for Persian avaliable to use. Persian-Avestan alphabet I have the app to interpret it downloaded on my phone and so can use it to type any Persian or English (phonetically) words into the script.  Tam\u00e2me afr\u00e2de ba\u0161ar \u00e2z\u00e2d be dony\u00e2 miy\u00e2yand va az lah\u00e2ze heysiyyat va hoquq b\u00e2 ham bar\u00e2barand, hame d\u00e2r\u00e2ye aqlo vejd\u00e2n mib\u00e2\u0161and va b\u00e2yad nesbat be yekdigar b\u00e2 ruhe bar\u00e2dari raft\u00e2r nem\u00e2yand.  N\u00e2m man Esfandy\u00e2r ast. Man az \u00car\u00e2n hastam.  Xodet\u00e2n r\u00e2 az se \u00e7\u00eaz behtar d\u00fbr nakon; Andi\u0161e n\u00eak, Goft\u00e2r n\u00eak \u00fb k\u00e2rd\u00e2r n\u00eak. - Pay\u00e2mbar Zarto\u0161t. ",
