            "answer_text": "I wanted to answer with no, but then I came across the Persian-Avestan alphabet which was developed by Louren\u00e7o Menezes D'Almeida. It is apparently perfectly fit for not only Avestan, but for writing Persian in it as well.   Persian-Avestan alphabet  Persian written in the Avestan alphabet (Article 1 of Human Rights declaration) Persian-Avestan alphabet Whether someone would take this seriously or not, it is interesting to see how Persian would look in this case. However, would Iranians switch to this script? No. Most likely if the time for a change comes, most would be for switching to the Latin alphabet. ",
